
transfer files securely

scp

scp username@<ip>:/remotepath /localpath
it will copy file from remote to our local machine


sftp it is part of ssh like scp. it os more interactive than scp

sftp username@<ip>
sftp> help  -> check the commands

sftp> get file.txt  -> download remote to your local current dir 

sftp> get -r Pictures/  -> download entirely dir

sftp> put file10.txt  -> upload local to remote, can use the flag -r for entirely dir



